                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18330905-87-off498 t18330905-87-crimeloc500"></join>, near St. Pauls, between three and four o'clock; I had seen the prisoner in company with two others; he and one more went and felt several gentleman's pockets - the prisoner then went behind an old gentleman and took this handkerchief from his pocket - I took the prisoner and the other; the prisoner then took the handkerchief and threw it on a horse's back; while I was getting it, the other lad got off, but I kept the prisoner.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. What he says is false; it was in the middle of Ludgate-hill.</p>
